diverging.description: Diverging colormaps with central neutral point and contrasting extremes
diverging.characteristics: Two contrasting hues, light middle, emphasizes deviations from center
diverging.pros: Strong contrast at extremes, emphasizes hot/cold boundaries, sharp transitions
diverging.cons: Middle values may lose definition, bimodal emphasis
diverging.expected_performance: Good - high contrast aids feature detection, especially at boundaries

qualitative.characteristics: Distinct colors, not ordered, designed for categories not continuous data
qualitative.pros: Maximum color distinction, each value highly distinguishable
qualitative.cons: Not designed for continuous thermal data, creates artificial segmentation
qualitative.expected_performance: Good - high contrast between values creates strong feature boundaries

sequential_multi_hue.description: Multi-hue sequential colormaps spanning color spectrum
sequential_multi_hue.characteristics: Multiple hues, varying luminance, wide perceptual range
sequential_multi_hue.pros: High dynamic range, distinct color transitions, good for temperature gradients
sequential_multi_hue.cons: Non-monotonic luminance can confuse feature detectors
sequential_multi_hue.expected_performance: Variable - depends on luminance profile and hue transitions

sequential_single_hue.description: Single-hue sequential colormaps with monotonic luminance
sequential_single_hue.characteristics: One primary hue, varying luminance and saturation
sequential_single_hue.pros: Maintains some gradient sharpness, intuitive temperature mapping
sequential_single_hue.cons: Limited color range, potential loss of detail in extreme values
sequential_single_hue.expected_performance: Moderate - better than perceptual but loses some feature definition

miscellaneous.characteristics: High contrast, discrete steps, unconventional color schemes
miscellaneous.pros: Maximum visual distinction, creates sharp boundaries
miscellaneous.cons: Arbitrary color mapping, may not represent thermal data meaningfully
miscellaneous.expected_performance: Unpredictable - high contrast helps but arbitrary mapping may confuse

grayscale.description: Single-channel intensity mapping preserving original thermal data
grayscale.pros: Preserves original intensity relationships, no color artifacts, optimal for feature detection
grayscale.cons: Limited perceptual range, harder to distinguish subtle temperature differences
grayscale.expected_performance: Best - maintains original gradient information crucial for feature matching

perceptual_uniform.description: Perceptually uniform colormaps designed for consistent visual interpretation
perceptual_uniform.pros: Beautiful visualization, perceptually uniform, scientifically sound for human interpretation
perceptual_uniform.cons: Smooths gradients too much, reduces sharp edges, diminishes feature distinctiveness
perceptual_uniform.expected_performance: Poor - perceptual uniformity eliminates sharp transitions needed for feature detection

cyclic.description: Cyclic colormaps for periodic data or angular measurements
cyclic.characteristics: Seamless wraparound, suitable for periodic phenomena
cyclic.pros: HSV provides maximum color variation, twilight has perceptual balance
cyclic.cons: May create artificial boundaries, HSV has luminance variations
cyclic.expected_performance: Variable - HSV better due to color diversity, twilight may smooth features
